reviews.text: Poor food quality with unreasonable price. Also, the service here is not so good.
Fair food quality, High priced, Extra Terrible service
Small little cozy place for some things BBQ or on stick. Decent priced and tasty.
Our favourite place ever! Love the lamb chop! I never eat lamp chop but since I had their first piece 8 years ago, I fell In love with lamb. Always great service.

Food is very slow to come out (like you'll forget you ordered it at times), but it's tasty enough and it's an experience to sit in this very localish place. The prices are what you would expect in Sai Ying Pun - not particularly cheap. It's worth a shot but I don't know if I would come here regularly.

reviews.text: Little spot with truly amazing seafood selection. Spare ribs are delicious 😋. Simple fast friendly service

Vast selection of BBQ and teppanyaki. I would recommend the clams, scallops, cod fish, chicken cartridge, and chicken wings. The porriage was excellent--century eggs with pork bone. Service was efficient and despite the crowd, the staff was corteous and responsive. Highly recommended if you're up for some local fare and feel.
